## рџљ¦ ROUTING & AUTH (CRITICAL)
- **REDIRECTS:** NEVER implement manual redirects to `/login` within page components; rely strictly on `src/proxy.ts` (formerly `middleware.ts`).
- **PROXY:** ALWAYS keep the `proxy.ts` matcher updated to exclude all public static assets (brand, manifest, robots.txt, etc).
- **AUTH STATE:** ALWAYS use the pre-fetched `initialUser` pattern in `RootLayout -> AuthProvider` to avoid redundant API hits.

## рџ“Ў DATA FETCHING (Vercel Architecture)
- **REACT QUERY:** ALWAYS use `@tanstack/react-query` for client-side data fetching and mutations. NEVER use SWR or `useEffect` for fetching.
- **EXPLICIT TYPING (MANDATORY):** ALWAYS provide explicit generic types to `useQuery<Data, Error>` and `apiFetch<Data>` to prevent build-time inference failures (e.g., getting inferred as `{}`).
- **QUERY CONSOLIDATION:** Consolidate related hooks into a single `use<Feature>Queries.ts` file per module (e.g., list and detail in one file). Do not fracture them.
- **RELATIVE URLS (MANDATORY):** Client-side `apiFetch` MUST use relative paths (`/api/v1/...`) to leverage the same-origin Next.js proxy, ensuring `SameSite=Strict` cookies are sent.
- **THIN SERVER:** `page.tsx` files should be thin Server Components. Keep data fetching in the thick client.
- **NO EDGE RUNTIME:** The project runs on Vercel Node.js runtime. Do NOT export `runtime = 'edge'` anywhere.
